wiki.summary: On “Overnight,” Logic describes the way many people falsely believe that he became famous overnight. He then goes on to explain why this belief is incorrect and says that it took years of hard work and dedication to get to where he is now. The song is the second one to be released by Logic in 2018, dropping just four days after his track “44 More.” The track was first released as a music video that was mostly recorded during Logic’s trips to Japan and Maui, while other parts of it were recorded on a plane. wiki.content: On “Overnight,” Logic describes the way many people falsely believe that he became famous overnight. He then goes on to explain why this belief is incorrect and says that it took years of hard work and dedication to get to where he is now. The song is the second one to be released by Logic in 2018, dropping just four days after his track “44 More.” The track was first released as a music video that was mostly recorded during Logic’s trips to Japan and Maui, while other parts of it were recorded on a plane. This song was first teased on Logic’s Snapchat story on February 28th, 2017, almost exactly one year prior to the song’s release. When asked about the release of the teased snippet, Logic responded on Twitter that it was never coming out. Read more on Last.fm.
